<br>
Pets will be neutral and no longer be aggro to mobs<br>
A person with /pet hold can make the pet not attack, no matter what happens.<br>
If the pet is neutral, and it never attacks, it will never go on the mobs hate list.<br>
<br>
So, does that mean you can summon companion at any time?  Even if pet is hit with AE dmg, or his master has been hit?<br>
<br>
Bascially, does only the mobs hate list determine if pet can be summoned?  Or will the pet not come if IT has something on its hatelist (which it is not attacking, because of /pet hold).<br>
<br>
If it works out, it would be possible to leave the pet anywhere and summon at anytime really.  Makes moving around pretty easy.  <br>
<br>
Somebody want to try and test this after patch?<br>
